
Certainly! Here's an example of an SCSS file for the `ErrorDialogComponent` to add some styling:

```scss
// error-dialog.component.scss
:host {
  display: block;
  max-width: 400px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  text-align: center;
  padding: 16px;
  background-color: #fff;
  box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
  border-radius: 8px;

  h2 {
    color: #ff3547;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  p {
    color: #333;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  button {
    color: #fff;
    background-color: #ff3547;
    border: none;
    padding: 8px 16px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background-color 0.3s;

    &:hover {
      background-color: #e02433;
    }
  }
}
```

Remember to import this SCSS file in your `ErrorDialogComponent` if you are using Angular CLI or a similar build system. Adjust the colors, fonts, and other styles to match your application's design.